<title>SWITZERLAND: Sulzer Medica buys Italian, Swiss units.</title>
<headline>Sulzer Medica buys Italian, Swiss units.</headline>
<dateline>WINTERTHUR, Switzerland 1997-03-06</dateline>
<text>
<p>Sulzer Medica, the medical technology division of Sulzer AG, said it had taken over Italian orthopaedic prostheses distributor Italpro S.p.A. and Swiss surgery supply company Synos Medical AG.</p>
<p>Sulzer Medica said buying Milan-based Italpro, with annual sales of about 50 million Swiss francs and a workforce of 30, would boost its Italian market share to 28 percent.</p>
<p>It said Synos Medical develops and distributes trauma products for casualty surgery, with 1996 sales of about six million Swiss francs.</p>
<p>-- Zurich Newsroom, +41-1-631 7340</p>
